!! Shared Productions

The following productions are referenced throughout the six child tiddlers. They are defined here once as a single point of reference so that the child grammars stay concise and consistent.

```
(* === Shared Terminal Productions === *)

StringLiteral   ::= '"""' AnyChar* '"""'
                  | '"' [^"]* '"'
                  | "'" [^']* "'"
                  | '[[' ( [^\]] | ']' [^\]] )* ']]'

Classes         ::= ( '.' ClassName )*
ClassName       ::= Letter ( Letter | Digit | '-' | '_' )*

StyleDefs       ::= ( PropertyName ':' PropertyValue ';' )*

(* === Shared Non-Terminal Productions === *)

InlineRun       ::= ( InlineRule | PlainText )*    (* inline wikitext until terminator *)
BlockContent    ::= ( Block | InlineRun | BlankLine )*    (* block-level wikitext until closing marker *)
PlainText       ::= AnyChar+    (* characters not starting an inline rule *)

(* === Character Classes === *)

Letter          ::= [a-zA-Z]
Digit           ::= [0-9]
AnyChar         ::= (* any character *)
WS              ::= [ \t]+    (* horizontal whitespace *)
SP              ::= [ \t]+    (* alias for WS *)
EOL             ::= '\r'? '\n' | EOF
Newline         ::= EOL
```

`StringLiteral` covers the four quoting forms used in widget attributes and filter parameters. `Classes` appears in image syntax, transclusions, and filtered transclusions to attach CSS classes. `StyleDefs` appears in style blocks and inline styles. The non-terminal productions (`InlineRun`, `BlockContent`, `PlainText`) describe the recursive structure the parser uses when it enters a new parsing context. The character classes provide the building blocks that the terminal productions above are composed from.